# Matex Security Rules

## Row Level Security (RLS) ‚Äî Mandatory
RLS MUST be enabled on every user-facing table before any policies are written.
Tables with RLS enabled: `auth_mcp.users`, `profile_mcp.profiles`, `listing_mcp.listings`, `bidding_mcp.bids`, `orders_mcp.orders`, `escrow_mcp.escrows`, `payments_mcp.transactions`, `messaging_mcp.threads`, `messaging_mcp.messages`, `notifications_mcp.notifications`.

**Before adding any new user-facing table:** `ALTER TABLE <schema>.<table> ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;`

## Sensitive Fields ‚Äî Never Expose in API Responses or Logs
| Table | Field |
|---|---|
| `auth_mcp.users` | `password_hash`, `mfa_secret` |
| `profile_mcp.bank_accounts` | `account_number_enc` |
| `kyc_mcp.documents` | `file_url` (use pre-signed URLs with expiry) |
| `auth_mcp.sessions` | `access_token_hash`, `refresh_token_hash` |
| `auth_mcp.password_resets` | `token_hash` |

`log-mcp` automatically sanitizes: passwords/tokens ‚Üí `[REDACTED]`, card numbers ‚Üí last 4 digits only, SIN/passport ‚Üí one-way hash.

